Squeezer application, a utility to copy and skim AnaNaS n-tuple files
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Author: Ph. Gras CEA/IRFU Saclay
Jan. 3, 11

Build the code:
---------------
make clean
make

Usage:
-----

Either use the default squeezer application or make your own code based on the CopyAnaTuple class.

To get help on the squeezer application, execute: 
squeezer --help to get help. 

See also makeskims --help. The program squeezer processes single input files. The makeksims uses the squeezer program
to process every file of one or several samples in one go.


When producing a data skim with squeezer application, the list of events is provided as an ascii file containing the run and event numbers.

